<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
(Figure 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Distribution map of Solanum michaelis." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.74.10159.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/110010" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">2</figureCitation>
). Endemic to Bolivia in the Departments of Tarija and Santa Cruz; although the species is to be expected in adjacent Paraguay. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saerkinen &amp; S. Knapp" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum michaelis" order="Solanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="michaelis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Solanum michaelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows in dry Chaco vegetation and in lower inter-Andean valleys, along slopes in sandy soils in mostly unshaded dry creek beds on bare soil, often in areas 
<pageBreakToken pageId="4" pageNumber="23" start="start">that</pageBreakToken>
have been burned, or in more humid Chaco vegetation at the edge of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“palmares”">&quot;palmares&quot;</normalizedToken>
(stands of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Morong" authorityYear="1893" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Copernicia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Copernicia alba" order="Arecales" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="23">Copernicia alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Morong) between 300-900 m elevation.
</paragraph>
